Ali Carter.label: Ali Carter
Ali Carter.description: Allister "Ali" Carter is an English professional snooker player, who lives in Chelmsford. He is a two-time World Championship runner-up, twice losing to Ronnie O'Sullivan, in 2008 and 2012. Wikipedia

Anthony Hamilton (snooker player).label: Anthony Hamilton
Anthony Hamilton (snooker player).description: Anthony Hamilton is an English professional snooker player noted for his strong break-building technique and distinctive appearance. Wikipedia

Barry Hawkins.label: Barry Hawkins
Barry Hawkins.description: Barry Hawkins is an English professional snooker player from Ditton in Kent. He turned professional in 1996, but only rose to prominence in the 2004/2005 snooker season, when he reached the last 16 of ... Wikipedia

Barry Pinches.label: Barry Pinches
Barry Pinches.description: Barry Pinches is an English professional snooker player, recognisable for his bright and flamboyant waistcoats, which usually feature the yellow and green colours of Norwich City F.C.. He is a former top 32 player and ranking-event quarter-finalist. Wikipedia

Chris Small.label: Chris Small
Chris Small.description: Christopher "Chris" Small is a retired Scottish professional snooker player and now a qualified snooker coach. His career was ended by the spinal condition ankylosing spondylitis. Wikipedia

David Gray (snooker player).label: David Gray
David Gray (snooker player).description: David Gray is an English snooker player. Wikipedia

Graeme Dott.label: Graeme Dott
Graeme Dott.description: Graeme Dott is a Scottish professional snooker player from Larkhall. He turned professional in 1994 and first entered the top 16 in 2001. Wikipedia

Jamie Cope.label: Jamie Cope
Jamie Cope.description: Jamie Cope is an English professional snooker player. He has reached the finals of two ranking tournaments. He has a fast, entertaining style of play, being nicknamed "Shotgun" due to his speed around the table and aggressive playing style. Wikipedia

Fergal O'Brien.label: Fergal O'Brien
Fergal O'Brien.description: Fergal O'Brien is an Irish professional snooker player. He has won one ranking title and reached two other major finals, and spent three seasons as a top 16 player. Wikipedia

Joe Perry (snooker player).label: Joe Perry
Joe Perry (snooker player).description: Joe Perry is an English professional snooker player. He is often referred to as the 'Fen Potter', nicknamed 'the Gentleman' for his likeable attitude and 'The Man from Sicily' for his dark quasi-Mediterranean features. Wikipedia

Judd Trump.label: Judd Trump
Judd Trump.description: Judd Trump is an English professional snooker player from Bristol and former world number one. He enjoyed considerable success in youth tournaments before turning professional in 2005. Wikipedia

Ken Doherty.label: Ken Doherty
Ken Doherty.description: Ken Doherty is an Irish professional snooker player and radio presenter. He is the only player ever to have been world amateur and world professional champion. He was also World Under-21 champion in 1989. Wikipedia

Mark Selby.label: Mark Selby
Mark Selby.description: Mark Anthony Selby is an English professional snooker and pool player. Runner up in the 2007 World Snooker Championship, he was the 2006 WEPF World Eight-ball Champion. Wikipedia

Mark King (snooker player).label: Mark King
Mark King (snooker player).description: Mark King is an English professional snooker player. He has not yet won a ranking tournament, but came close when he was a beaten finalist in the 1997 Regal Welsh Open and the 2004 Irish Masters. Wikipedia

Quinten Hann.label: Quinten Hann
Quinten Hann.description: Quinten Hann is an Australian former professional snooker player who now plays professional pool. He was the 1999 WEPF World Eight-ball Champion and 1994 world under 21 champion. His highest break is 143. Wikipedia

Robert Milkins.label: Robert Milkins
Robert Milkins.description: Robert Milkins is an English professional snooker player from Gloucester. Milkins is currently ranked at world number 14. Wikipedia

Stephen Hendry.label: Stephen Hendry
Stephen Hendry.description:
Stephen Gordon Hendry MBE is a Scottish former professional snooker player.
Hendry became the youngest professional snooker player in 1985 aged 15 and, in 1990, he was the youngest-ever snooker World Champion, at the age of 21. Wikipedia

Stephen Lee.label: Stephen Lee
Stephen Lee.description: Stephen Lee is a banned professional snooker-player from Trowbridge, Wiltshire, England. He turned professional in 1992 and was ranked in the top 16 between the 1997/1998 and 2007/2008 snooker seasons, ... Wikipedia

Steve Davis.label: Steve Davis
Steve Davis.description: Steve Davis, OBE is an English professional snooker player from Plumstead, London. Known for dominating the sport during the 1980s, when he won the World Championship six times and was ranked world ... Wikipedia
Awards: BBC Sports Personality of the Year Award

Tony Drago.label: Tony Drago
Tony Drago.description: Tony Drago is a professional snooker and pool player from Malta. He won the 2003 World Pool Masters Tournament beating Hsia Hui-kai 8–6 and also reached the quarter finals of the World Snooker Championship. Wikipedia

Adam Duffy.label: Adam Duffy
Adam Duffy.description:
Adam Duffy is an English professional snooker player.
Duffy qualified for the 2011/2012 professional Main Tour as one of four semi-finalists from the third and final Q School event. Wikipedia

Adrian Gunnell.label: Adrian Gunnell
Adrian Gunnell.description: Adrian Gunnell is an English professional snooker player from Telford. He has reached the last-16 in four world ranking events, but has yet to progress beyond that stage. He has yet to qualify for the final stages of the World Championship. Wikipedia

Andy Hicks.label: Andy Hicks
Andy Hicks.description: Andy Hicks is an English professional snooker player. Nicknamed "The Cream of Devon", he has been a World Snooker Championship semi-finalist and was ranked within the world's top 32 for many seasons but has never broken into the top 16. Wikipedia

Cao Yupeng.label: Cao Yupeng
Cao Yupeng.description: Cao Yupeng is a professional snooker player from the People's Republic of China. He won the 2011 Asian Under-21 Championship, thus qualifying for the professional Main Tour for the 2011/2012 season. Wikipedia

Ben Woollaston.label: Ben Woollaston
Ben Woollaston.description: Ben Woollaston is an English professional snooker player from Leicester. Wikipedia

Chris McBreen.label: Chris McBreen
Chris McBreen.description: Chris McBreen is a professional New Zealand snooker player, living in Germany. He was runner-up in the Oceania Play-Offs, however Glen Wilkinson who beat him decided not take his place on the Main Tour. Wikipedia

David Grace (snooker player).label: David Grace
David Grace (snooker player).description: David Grace is an English professional snooker player. After being a successful junior and amateur player, he became a professional in 2008, gaining his place by winning the 2008 European Snooker Championships against Craig Steadman. Wikipedia

Gary Owen (snooker player).label: Gary Owen
Gary Owen (snooker player).description:
Gary Owen was a Welsh snooker player.
Owen first emerged as the inaugural British Under-16 champion in 1944 and reached the final of the prestigious English Amateur championship six years later. Wikipedia

Jackie Rea.label: Jackie Rea
Jackie Rea.description: Jack 'Jackie' Rea was a snooker player from Northern Ireland. Wikipedia

Corey Deuel.label: Corey Deuel
Corey Deuel.description: Corey Deuel is an American professional pocket billiards player from West Jefferson, Ohio. Nicknamed "Cash Money", he is an accomplished tournament competitor, having won the US Open Nine-ball Championship ... Wikipedia
Corey Deuel.Born: November 20, 1977 (age 36), Santa Barbara, California, United States

Jak Jones.label: Jak Jones
Jak Jones.description:
Jak Jones is a Welsh professional snooker player.
Jones was born in Cwmbran, Wales. He became a professional in 2010 at the age of 16, by winning the 2010 European Under 19 Snooker Championship in Malta. Wikipedia

John Virgo.label: John Virgo
John Virgo.description: John Virgo is an English former professional snooker player and more recently a snooker commentator and TV personality. Wikipedia
John Virgo.Born: March 3, 1946 (age 68), Salford, Greater Manchester, United Kingdom

Joe Swail.label: Joe Swail
Joe Swail.description: Joe Swail is a professional snooker player from Belfast, Northern Ireland. He has reached ten major ranking semi-finals, including the 2000 and 2001 World Championships but only one final. Wikipedia

Jamie O'Neill (snooker player).label: Jamie O'Neill
Jamie O'Neill (snooker player).description: Jamie O'Neill is an English professional snooker player who lives in Wellingborough. Wikipedia

Karen Corr.label: Karen Corr
Karen Corr.description: Karen Corr is a professional billiards player representing Northern Ireland, and was inducted in the BCA Hall of Fame in 2012. Wikipedia

Kurt Maflin.label: Kurt Maflin
Kurt Maflin.description: Kurt Graham Maflin is a Norwegian professional snooker player of English descent. A strong break-builder, Maflin is among 20 players to have made multiple 147 breaks in professional competition. Wikipedia

Liu Chuang.label: Liu Chuang
Liu Chuang.description: Liu Chuang is a Chinese professional snooker player. Wikipedia

Liu Song (snooker player).label: Liu Song
Liu Song (snooker player).description: Liu Song is a professional snooker player from Tianjin, China. Wikipedia

Mark Allen (snooker player).label: Mark Allen
Mark Allen (snooker player).description: Mark Allen is a Northern Irish professional snooker player. He won the World Amateur Championship in 2004. The following year he entered the Main Tour and took only three seasons to reach the elite top 16. Wikipedia

Mark Joyce.label: Mark Joyce
Mark Joyce.description: Mark Joyce is an English professional snooker player who lives in Walsall. He began his professional career by playing Challenge Tour in 2003. Wikipedia

Martin Gould.label: Martin Gould
Martin Gould.description: Martin Gould is an English professional snooker player from Pinner in the London Borough of Harrow. He practises at the Whetstone Snooker Club. He works part-time as a debt collector. Wikipedia

Matthew Selt.label: Matthew Selt
Matthew Selt.description: Matthew Selt is an English professional snooker player from Romford. He qualified for the professional tour by finishing seventh on the Pontin’s International Open Series in 2006/2007. Wikipedia

Mei Xiwen.label: Mei Xiwen
Mei Xiwen.description: Mei Xiwen is a Chinese professional snooker player. He made his debut on the Main Tour in the 2009/2010 season, as the ACBS Asian nomination, but dropped off the tour after just one season. Wikipedia

Michaela Tabb.label: Michaela Tabb
Michaela Tabb.description: Michaela Tabb is a Scottish professional snooker and pool referee who has established significant milestones for female officials in cue sports. In 2002, she became the first woman to referee at a professional ranking snooker tournament. Wikipedia

Michael White (snooker player).label: Michael White
Michael White (snooker player).description: Michael White is a Welsh professional snooker player from Neath. Wikipedia

Mike Hallett.label: Mike Hallett
Mike Hallett.description: Mike Hallett is an English professional snooker player and television sports commentator. Wikipedia

Nigel Bond.label: Nigel Bond
Nigel Bond.description: Nigel Bond is an English professional snooker player. He was ranked within the top 16 from 1992 to 1999. After a season outside the top 32, he regained his place there. Wikipedia

Paul Davies (snooker player).label: Paul Davies
Paul Davies (snooker player).description: Paul Davies is a retired Welsh professional snooker player who lives in Cardiff. He turned professional in 1991, making him one of the longest-standing players on the game's Main Tour. Wikipedia

Robin Hull.label: Robin Hull
Robin Hull.description: Robin Hull is a Finnish professional snooker player. For some time he was the sole Nordic player on the game's main tour.Robin was born and raised in Finland, to a Finnish mother and English father. Wikipedia

Rod Lawler.label: Rod Lawler
Rod Lawler.description: Rod Lawler is an English professional snooker player. He is noted for his very slow play, which has led to him being nicknamed "Rod the Plod". Wikipedia

Sam Baird.label: Sam Baird
Sam Baird.description: Sam Baird is a professional snooker player from England. He first entered the professional tour for the 2009/10 season, by winning the EBSA Pro-Ticket Tour Play-Offs. Wikipedia

Sam Craigie.label: Sam Craigie
Sam Craigie.description: Sam Craigie is an English professional snooker player from Newcastle. He enjoyed a successful junior career before turning professional in 2011. Wikipedia

Shokat Ali.label: Shaukat Ali
Shokat Ali.description:
Shaukat Ali Khan is a Pakistani folk singer.
Born into a family of artists in Malakwal, Ali began singing while at college in the 1960s, receiving help from his elder brother Inayat Ali Khan. Wikipedia

Simon Bedford.label: Simon Bedford
Simon Bedford.description: Simon Bedford is an English professional snooker player. His best run to date in a professional ranking event was to qualify for the 1998 World Championship beating Gary Wilkinson 10–9, before losing 10–6 to Steve Davis. Wikipedia

Steve Prest.label: Steve Prest
Steve Prest.description: Steve Prest was an English professional snooker player and coach. Wikipedia

Tom Dennis.label: Tom Dennis
Tom Dennis.description:
Tom Dennis was an English professional snooker and English billiards player.
Dennis reached the finale of the World Championship in 1927, 1929, 1930 and 1931 but was beaten every time by Joe Davis. Wikipedia

Tony Knowles (snooker player).label: Tony Knowles
Tony Knowles (snooker player).description: Anthony Knowles is an English professional snooker player. He was a three times semi-finalist in the World Professional Snooker Championship in the 1980s. Wikipedia

Troy Shaw.label: Troy Shaw
Troy Shaw.description: Troy Shaw is an English professional snooker player. Shaw won the second leg of minor ranking tournament the Strachan Challenge in 1993, beating Nigel Bond in the final. Wikipedia

Walter Donaldson (snooker player).label: Walter Donaldson
Walter Donaldson (snooker player).description:
Walter Donaldson was a Scottish professional snooker player.
Born in Coatbridge, North Lanarkshire, he was the first Scottish-born player to make a mark in the world of snooker. Wikipedia

Wendy Jans.label: Wendy Jans
Wendy Jans.description: Wendy Jans is a Belgian amateur snooker and pool player. Wikipedia

Zhang Anda.label: Zhang Anda
Zhang Anda.description:
Zhang Anda is a Chinese professional snooker player, who made his debut on the Main Tour for the 2009/2010 season. He qualified by winning the ACBS Asian Under-21 Championship.
Standing at 5 ft 3ins tall, he is nicknamed "Mighty Mouse". Wikipedia

Brendan O'Donoghue.label: Brendan O'Donoghue
Brendan O'Donoghue.description: Brendan O'Donoghue is an Irish professional snooker player. He hails from Nenagh. He first entered the professional tour for the 2009/10 season. Wikipedia

Declan Hughes.label: Declan Hughes
Declan Hughes.description: Declan Hughes is an Irish novelist, playwright and screenwriter. His most widely known crime novels centre around the Irish-American detective Ed Loy. Wikipedia
Awards: Shamus Award for Best First P. I. Novel
Nominations: Theakston's Old Peculier Crime Novel of the Year Award
Shamus Award for Best P. I. Hardcover Novel
Macavity Awards for Best Mystery NovelMore

Hitesh Naran.label: Hitesh Naran
Hitesh Naran.description: Hitesh Naran is a South African amateur snooker player who won the South African Snooker Championship twice, and was the first unified champion of South Africa. Wikipedia

James Tatton.label: James Tatton
James Tatton.description: James Tatton is an English professional snooker player. He turned professional in 1996 and his highest break is 142. Wikipedia

Jason Ferguson (snooker player).label: Jason Ferguson
Jason Ferguson (snooker player).description: Jason Ferguson is a former professional snooker player. He reached the World Snooker Championship on three occasions, and was for four seasons ranked in the world's top 32 players, reaching a peak position of #28. Wikipedia

Justin Astley.label: Justin Astley
Justin Astley.description: Justin Astley is an English professional snooker player. He played on Challenge Tour in 2001/02, and first qualified for the Main Tour in 2002/03, but lost his place. Then he played on Challenge Tour again from 2003 to 2005. Wikipedia

Kyren Wilson.label: Kyren Wilson
Kyren Wilson.description: Kyren Wilson is an English professional snooker player. He turned professional in 2010, after finishing fifth in the 2009/2010 PIOS rankings. Wikipedia

Lu Ning.label: Lu Ning
Lu Ning.description: Lu Ning is an amateur snooker player from the People's Republic of China. Wikipedia

Stephen Rowlings.label: Stephen Rowlings
Stephen Rowlings.description: Stephen Rowlings is a professional snooker player from Preston. He first entered the professional tour for the 2009/10 season. Wikipedia
Stephen Rowlings.Born: February 4, 1976 (age 38), City of Preston, Lancashire, United Kingdom

Bernard Bennett.label: Bernard Bennett
Bernard Bennett.description: Bernard Bennett was an English professional player of snooker and English billiards, for almost 30 years. Bennett played an important role, but an often unsung one, in the development of snooker and billiards during the 1970s and early 80s. Wikipedia

Adam Wicheard.label: Adam Wicheard
Adam Wicheard.description: Adam Wicheard is an English professional snooker player, who has competed professionally since 2010. Wikipedia

Alain Robidoux.label: Alain Robidoux
Alain Robidoux.description: Alain Robidoux is a Canadian snooker player; he played on the World Snooker tour from 1988 to 2005 and continues to play in events in Canada. Wikipedia

Alex Higgins.label: Alex Higgins
Alex Higgins.description: Alexander Gordon "Alex" Higgins was a Northern Irish professional snooker player who was twice World Champion and twice runner-up. He earned the nickname Hurricane Higgins because of his speed of play. Wikipedia
Nominations: BBC Sports Personality of the Year Award

Andy Lee (snooker player).label: Andy Lee
Andy Lee (snooker player).description: Andy Lee is an English professional snooker player from Hinckley, born 27 November 1980. He has qualified for the main tour for the 2008/2009 season by beating Adam Duffy 6–3 in the 2008 English Pro Ticket Tour Play-offs. Wikipedia

Atthasit Mahitthi.label: Atthasit Mahitthi
Atthasit Mahitthi.description:
Atthasit Mahitthi is a professional Thai snooker player.
Mahitthi reached the semi-final at the 2006 IBSF World Amateur Championship in Amman, Jordan, where he was eliminated by Kurt Maflin 8–4. Wikipedia

Au Chi-wai.label: Au Chi-wai
Au Chi-wai.description: Au Chi-wai, is an amateur snooker and pool player from Hong Kong. In snooker, he won, the silver medal in the snooker doubles event at the 2002 Asian Games in Busan. Au was also the second runner-up in the 2009 Asian Snooker Championships. Wikipedia

Bjorn Haneveer.label: Bjorn Haneveer
Bjorn Haneveer.description: Bjorn Haneveer is a Belgian retired professional snooker player. Haneveer now plays at semi-professional level and also commentates on snooker matches for Dutch Eurosport. Wikipedia

Bob Chaperon.label: Bob Chaperon
Bob Chaperon.description: Robert "Bob" Chaperon is a retired Canadian professional snooker and billiards player. Wikipedia

Bogdan Wołkowski.label: Bogdan Wołkowski
Bogdan Wołkowski.description: Bogdan Wołkowski, nicknamed "The Wizard", is a Polish professional billiards trick-shot artist and entertainer, who has won many World Trick Shot Championships. Wikipedia

Brian Morgan (snooker player).label: Brian Morgan
Brian Morgan (snooker player).description: Brian Morgan is an English professional snooker player and coach. He is a former World Under-21 champion, and was among the top 32 players in the professional world rankings for several years. Wikipedia

Clive Everton.label: Clive Everton
Clive Everton.description: Clive Everton is a Welsh veteran former BBC snooker commentator, journalist and author. He began his BBC career on the radio but is best known for his television work, commentating on the World Snooker Championship from 1978 until 2010. Wikipedia

Colm Gilcreest.label: Colm Gilcreest
Colm Gilcreest.description: Colm Gilcreest is a former professional snooker player from Kilmainhamwood, County Meath, Ireland. Wikipedia

Daniel Ward (snooker player).label: Daniel Ward
Daniel Ward (snooker player).description: Daniel Ward is a notable English amateur snooker player, with one international title, who has reached the amateur World Championship final round, in 2006. Wikipedia

Dave Finbow.label: Dave Finbow
Dave Finbow.description: David "Dave" Finbow is a former English professional snooker player from Worcester. In his career he managed to beat players such as Ronnie O'Sullivan, Ken Doherty and James Wattana. Wikipedia

David Gilbert (snooker player).label: David Gilbert
David Gilbert (snooker player).description: David Brown Gilbert is an English professional snooker player. Gilbert is a former World Snooker Young Player of Distinction. Gilbert practices in Tamworth, Staffordshire, at Tamworth Cue Sports Leisure Club. Wikipedia

David Hogan (snooker player).label: David Hogan
David Hogan (snooker player).description: David Hogan is an Irish professional snooker player currently residing in Borrisokane. He first entered the professional tour for the 2009/10 season, by winning the 2009 EBSA European Championship but dropped off the same season. Wikipedia

David Morris (snooker player).label: David Morris
David Morris (snooker player).description: David Morris, born in Kilkenny, Ireland, on 27 November 1988, is an Irish snooker player. Wikipedia

Dick Jaspers.label: Dick Jaspers
Dick Jaspers.description: Dingeman Jacobus Johannes "Dick" Jaspers is a Dutch professional carom billiards player who specializes in the three-cushion event. Wikipedia

Dechawat Poomjaeng.label: Dechawat Poomjaeng
Dechawat Poomjaeng.description: Dechawat Poomjaeng is a Thai professional snooker player. Wikipedia

Euan Henderson.label: Euan Henderson
Euan Henderson.description:
Euan Henderson is a retired Scottish professional snooker player.
In his twelve-year professional career he reached only one ranking final, in the 1996 Grand Prix, albeit without beating any of the game's established leading players. Wikipedia

Francisco Bustamante.label: Francisco Bustamante
Francisco Bustamante.description: Francisco Bustamante is a Filipino professional pocket billiards player from Tarlac, and the 2010 World Nine-ball Champion, nicknamed "Django", after the lead character of the film of the same name, ... Wikipedia

Doug Mountjoy.label: Doug Mountjoy
Doug Mountjoy.description: Doug Mountjoy is a retired Welsh snooker player. Although he only won two ranking titles, he did so in successive tournaments in 1988/1989 – and while in his mid 40s. Wikipedia
